# WHY go-git/go-git IS A DISTINCTIVE AXIS-43
# CONTINUATION:
#
#   github.com/go-git/go-git by the go-git
#   organization (originally src-d, now a community
#   org after src-d's dissolution) is the de-facto
#   pure-Go git implementation, predating its Rust
#   counterpart (gix) by several years and
#   establishing the design pattern of "implement
#   git's data model + wire protocol from scratch
#   rather than wrapping libgit2."  Distinguishing
#   characteristics:
#     1. PURE GO — zero CGo, zero libgit2 .so
#        dependency; statically-linked Go binaries
#        Just Work everywhere Go supports
#     2. PLAINOPEN + PLAININIT + PLAINCLONE API —
#        `git.PlainOpen(path)` opens an existing
#        repo; `git.PlainInit(path, isBare)` creates
#        one; `git.PlainClone(path, isBare,
#        &git.CloneOptions{URL: "https://..."})`
#        clones.  Clean, focused API surface for
#        the common case
#     3. STORAGE-AGNOSTIC — `git.Open(storer,
#        worktree)` allows arbitrary storage backends
#        (in-memory via go-billy/memfs, S3 via
#        custom Storer, in-process REST via gRPC,
#        etc.) — the same code works across storage
#        plumbing
#     4. STREAMING PACKFILE READING — packfile
#        reading is streaming-friendly; large packs
#        don't require buffering the full file in
#        memory; suitable for memory-constrained
#        deployments (Lambda, CloudRun, embedded)
#     5. REFERENCE ITERATION — `repo.References()`
#        returns an iterator of refs; same for
#        Branches/Tags/Remotes/Worktrees; idiomatic
#        Go iteration patterns
#     6. SSH + HTTPS + LOCAL PROTOCOLS — supports
#        all standard git transport protocols
#        including SSH key authentication via
#        x/crypto/ssh
#     7. ~6,200+ STARS ON go-git/go-git
#     8. ECOSYSTEM-DOMINANT — used by argoproj/
